broader educational ‘reform’ efforts; • examples of how early state-wide mandates impacted teacher professional development; • a presentation of how new university-level teacher preparation curricula misaligns with commonly-held beliefs about what teachers of language minority students should know and understand; • an exploration of principals’ concerns about enforcing top-down policies for SEI implementation; • an investigation of what SEI policy looks like in today’s classrooms and whether it constitutes equity; • and finally, a discussion of what the various cases mean for the education of English learners in the state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEducation, BilingualzArizonavCase studies. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxImmersion methodvCase studies. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingzArizonaxForeign speakersvCase studies. 0aLanguage policyzArizonavCase studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aArizona.  aStructured English Immersion.  alanguage education.  alanguage policy.1 aArias, Beatriz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrijalva, Giovanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHogan, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJimenez-Silva, Margarita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLillie, Karen E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarkos, Amy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Sarah C. K., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoore, Sarah Catherine K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiley, Terrence G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWr